# View.elm — EARLY

HTML rendering of a LynRummy board and its cards. Faithful
port of the `render_*` pure-drawing functions in
`angry-cat/src/lyn_rummy/game/game.ts` (lines ~945–1180).

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. First visible surface; expected to evolve
  as we wire turn chrome, hand zone, action buttons.
- **Source:** game.ts render_card_char / render_playing_card /
  render_wing / render_card_stack / render_board /
  render_board_heading. Action buttons deferred.

## What's in this first pass

- `viewCard : Card -> Html msg` — a single playing card. Two
  stacked text divs (value + suit emoji), red/black color,
  white bg, `1px blue solid` border, 27px × 40px, 17px font.
- `viewWing : Html msg` — invisible zero-width placeholder for
  drop targets. Kept for faithful structure even though no
  drag yet.
- `viewStack : CardStack -> Html msg` — position-absolute div
  at `stack.loc.top` / `stack.loc.left`; contains
  [left wing, cards with 2px margin-left between, right wing].
  Incomplete stacks get a gray tint (faithful).
- `viewBoard : List CardStack -> Html msg` — the khaki
  container with `#000080` border, 15px border-radius, 540px
  height, `position: relative`.
- `viewBoardHeading : Html msg` — "Board" text in bold navy
  19px.

## Deferred from the TS source

- Action buttons (complete turn / undo / hint / replay).
- Hand-card row + hand advice.
- Drag handles / cursors (arrive with drag/drop work).
- Mergeable-stack highlights (arrive with drag-over).

## Elm divergences from TS

- Imperative `document.createElement("div"); div.style.foo = bar`
  → declarative `div [ style "foo" "bar" ] [...]`.
- TS mutates styles post-construction (e.g.,
  `card_span.style.marginLeft = "2px"` on all but the first
  card in a stack). Elm passes the margin as an extra
  attribute to `viewPlayingCard`.
- TS nests DOM nodes inside a card div (value div + suit
  div); Elm mirrors that structure exactly.
- `set_common_card_styles` TS helper → inline list of
  `style` attributes in `viewPlayingCard`. Inlined for
  single-call-site clarity.

## Pointers

- Consumer: `Main.elm` wires view into `Browser.element`.
- Depends on: `LynRummy.Card.valueDisplayStr`,
  `LynRummy.Card.suitEmojiStr`, `LynRummy.Card.cardColor`,
  `LynRummy.CardStack.incomplete`.
- TS reference: game.ts lines 945–1180 (the `PURE DRAWING
  CODE` section).
